**Key architectural decisions made in Phase 3:**
- RRF (Reciprocal Rank Fusion) replaces separate BM25+semantic merge — single PostgreSQL query
- `ts_rank_cd` (cover density) replaces `ts_rank` — rewards proximity of query terms
- Trigram (`pg_trgm`) added as third RRF signal for name similarity
- `identifier_namespace` filter applied when query contains "tag"/"component"
- Confidence threshold (default 0.105, in `system.json`) — below threshold returns top 5 with "no exact match" message
- Python reranker skipped for structured collections — RRF handles ranking
- `quant` removed from synonyms.json (was breaking BM25 queries)
- Docs have no schema files (unlike XML/tables) — doc collections use folder structure as category
- Discovery list/count correct for content queries — vault analytics need metadata query path (Phase 4.6)
- LLM intent now returns role + target — replaces field_maps.json keyword matching
- LLM intent prompt: singular "tag"/"field" = answer; plural "tags"/"fields" = discovery_list
- Discovery table headers: derived from payload fields (identifier_field, primary_name_field) — no hardcoding
- All structured serializers store primary_name_field and type_field in payload
- tsvector trigger preprocesses slashes to spaces for correct tokenization
- Shared payload enrichment (payload_utils.py) adds category, folder_path, primary_name_field, type_field to all serializer outputs — foundation for cross-linking
- Discovery table headers derived from payload fields (identifier_field, primary_name_field) — no hardcoding; works for all collections
- Schema storage: PostgreSQL schemas table is primary store; disk JSON files are legacy backup only; LLM inference runs when no schema exists anywhere
- Link index skipped for tables > 2,000 rows — O(n²) cross-referencing only appropriate for small structured reference datasets (FIX, RECON)
- Cross-link builder: Option C (manual trigger) then Option B (background thread after ingest) — not synchronous during ingestion
- Batch embedding: batch_size=32 for LM Studio stability with BGE-large
- PDF/image/astro parsers all functional; ingest verified against test files

