## Phase 4 Architecture Decisions — Deployment & Data Sources (open, captured 2026-06-15, refined 2026-06-16)

Recorded for when the system is proven and ready for blind testing. NAS remains always-available dev/fallback environment.

### Deployment / hosting
- Target users: multiple people on Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD) sessions, same company tenant.
- **Data-AVD and login-AVD are likely DISTINCT** — app stays a remote-DB client.
- AVD-hosting dissolves "compiled installer" concern — provision-once, users open in browser.
- UI framework: Streamlit stays; Open WebUI candidate when MCP server ready (Phase 4.7).
- HTML-in-Streamlit pragmatic path for richer views.

### Data sources
- Current: file ingestion (XML, XLSX, CSV, Markdown).
- Future: Halo + Confluence (API access confirmed) + Snowflake.
- Keep ingestion-source boundary clean — new sources plug in as adapters.
- Once ingested via MCP adapters, data uses same Postgres schema — metadata query path covers it for free.

### Guardrail
- Protect the core/UI separation religiously.
- **NAS-AI is fully local. No external AI or cloud model connections, ever.**
